properties.Name: PartyBiometric
properties.Description: The automatic recognition of individual parties based on unique combinations of measurable physical or behavioral characteristics. Examples include fingerprints, iris scanning, face and voice recognition, or hand geometry.

Columns.Name: PartyId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Party.

Columns.Name: BiometricTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a biometric type.

Columns.Name: Timestamp
Columns.Description: The timestamp that the associated information is reported, recorded or effective as-of.

Columns.Name: PartyBiometricTemplate
Columns.Description:
The biometric template is the  pattern of a party of the associated biometric stored for matching. 

BioCert devices convert fingerprint information into mathematical templates, so actual fingerprint images are not stored and cannot be reconstructed based on template data.

Columns.Name: PartyBiometricNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the party biometric.
